tip.text: Friendly staff, pleasant atmosphere, a bit pricey (even for airport food), and lacking character. Food was well executed, but lacking style & originality. Shrimp stir fry was generic, but not bad.
Although pricey ($9 for 6 pieces) spicy tuna roll was fresh, nice heat, met expectations.  Also ordered curry chicken dumplings (4 pieces for $10), they are what you'd expect, but nothing special.
Great fish & chips, especially in an airport! Nice atmosphere, and delicious draft brews to boot. Be sure to stop here for a bite while waiting for your flight
Get the Texas Ranger tacos, and don't forget to mix your salsas (orange + green) together!
Ordered the ceviche and the suckling pig, both were fantastic! Truly can't go wrong with anything off the menu, even dessert was delicious (order the churros)!
Huevos Ahogados! A delicious soup consisting of poached eggs in a chipotle broth with avocado, onions, cilantro & sour cream. I like to throw the beans into the soup too!
Absolutely fabulous Huevos Rancheros! The Huevos Ahogados is a large breakfast soup which is my other go to. Friendly service and great prices make this a favorite of mine.
Great for a quick bite to eat, not really a sit down place. Got the "death by tikka" and it was quite delicious. Naan was a bit spongy for my taste, but still enjoyable. Would go back!
Great fajitas! Some of the best service I've had in a while. Only downside is that it is a bit expensive, but that comes with airport food. Will come back on my next PHX layover for sure!
